to the editor re in jfk file hidden illness pain and pills front page nov 17 is n't it time the kennedy image protectors allowed broad access to information about this president he is a historical figure and 39 years after his death there seems no reason to restrict access to such information i note that his medical records were reviewed only by someone who appears to be writing a favorable biography about kennedy one who despite the negative information found it necessary to say it did not impair kennedy 's judgment in the cuban missile crisis the people controlling access are those who have spent their lives denying the truth about this and other problems of kennedy 's and some still wonder why the american public is suspicious of any pronouncements about the personal lives of those still active in public life donald s brooks boca raton fla nov 18 2002

